args:
Mordecai goes berserk with hate and attacks
the Holywyrm, but Ilia miraculously awakens
as they battle. She attempts to rescue her
friend from his emotions, but his hate itself
then transforms into the Other and attempts
to destroy the world.
It is the Other—it is Morsayati.
The name of the calamity you spoke of...
Yes. To put an end to a long, long war,\nhumanity summoned a calamity from the\nends of the otherworld.
This tale was spoken of in history—and I,\nbelieving it, thought I had to fix this world.
But I was wrong. The history I believed\nin was naught but a travesty.
The true history—the reality of the Other's\nsummoning—was this!
Don't cry, just run! Just run and—HRK!
Mommy turned into a fiend! Waaaah!
Black mana is gushing out of the cave\nand withering all the trees!
What have you done, humans...?\nWhat force have you offended...?
This black mana makes me feel like\nI'm going to go out of my mind!
Hold on to your wits!\nWe must put a stop to this!
This power is not bound by the rules of this\nworld. It is outside my control.
Holywyrm! If you would proclaim yourself\nruler over the world, then I should think\nyou have something you must do now!
I am aware. However, I have decided that\nthe power of the otherworld should not be\neliminated at this time.
Then you mean to stand by and watch\nthe destruction wrought by Mordecai?!
This is a prime opportunity to wash away\nall of the corruption that has built up,\nalong with the distortion.

The human whelps have grown too much.
Their civilization is beyond them, so I will
permit this to wash it away and create a
new world from the ashes.
Such a deed ill befits one who would\ncall himself the Holywyrm!
It is for the world—and by extension,\nit is for your sakes as well, humans.

In a history that has progressed in the
proper fashion, you human whelps will
eventually prosper rather than bring
ruination to all.
You there! Outcast from another world!\nWield your power freely!
Under his influence, black mana is\ngushing forth all over the world.
It is the end of everything...
And so, the battle began between the Holywyrm\nElysium and Morsayati, and it raged for seven\nwhole days and nights.

They moved from one part of the world to another
as their mighty struggle unfolded. Yet perhaps this
was as Elysium had planned: A way to wash the
world clean and bring about its rebirth.
In the wake of this battle, many cities were\ndestroyed, numerous lives were lost, and the\nonce-mighty civilization crumbled.
Yet in an ironic twist, the people saw Elysium\nas their last and only hope, for it was he who\nbattled against the Other.
In my time, Elysium is viewed as a symbol\nof order and harmony, and believed to be\na guardian of the world.
I simply could not imagine he would\ndo something so callous as this.
It is true that the Holywyrm is unfeeling,\nbut not necessarily UNTRUE that he\nis a symbol of order and harmony.
He seeks a perfect world—yet a perfect\nworld is also an immutable one.
In his eyes, he sees the growth and\nprogress of life as no more than a force\nwhich will distort his perfection.

And that's why he's trying to eradicate
the people who have achieved progress
from the world? That does not seem like
a just act to me.
Yep. Thought I was pretty dead myself,\nbut looks like I'm actually...fine?
You're NOT fine! You can barely stand!
Yeah, but I can't just cozy up in bed;\nthe world is hanging by a string right now.
Ilia, what did you mean when you said\nthe Holywyrm is worried?
Just that. See, in the beginning,\nElysium wanted to get rid of Mordecai.
But now Mordecai's influence is spreading\naround the world more than expected.
Dragons are going berserk, humans are\ntransforming into fiends...
It's a complete breakdown of order\nand harmony.
Elysium wants to find some way to\ndo away with all of that.
You speak with such confidence.\nHow can you know this?
Maybe it's the pact? I dunno, but I can\njust...tell what Elysium is thinking.
So I decided to take advantage of it.
I'll create an organization—no, a religion!\nOne that reveres the Holywyrm\nand reviles the Other!
To deal with all the various disasters\ncaused by Mordecai's influence.
I'll clean up the world the way Elysium\nwants and have humanity take\nresponsibility for keeping watch over it.
By giving them that role and incorporating\nthem into the system of Elysium's world...
It will make it so that Elysium can't just\ndestroy everyone. ...Good plan, no?
I can hardly believe you were thinking\nof such a thing...
(Is this the beginning of the Ilian Church?!\nI never would have dreamt of it starting\nin such a mad fashion...)
And where, exactly, ARE you going\nwhen you can barely stand?!
Isn't it obvious? To Mordecai.\nI have to help him.
Go with the blessings of the Goddess Ilia.
Give Ilia back, Elysium! If you do not,\nI will tear this world from your grasp!
I'm right here! You don't have to do that!

Ilia! You're alive!
—No, Ilia died.
We can be together again!
—She was stolen from me.
I'm so glad my words reached you...
I was a prisoner of my hate. But when I\nheard your voice, I remembered myself.
But the hatred is too great; it still exists.
You have complex emotions, like anyone.\nThis dispersed your power, but in the end,\nalso controlled it.
However, losing Ilia meant all your power\nwas poured into your hatred for Elysium.
And that is the calamity:\nThe Other, Morsayati.
We have to stop him. For the world,\nand for Morsayati himself.
I'm going, too; there are people in the\nfuture of this world that I would protect\nwith my life.
Then let's do it together.\nLet's show him our love.

Our love will never be defeated by a being
of pure hate—and if Elysium thinks things
will go just like HE'S planning, he's got a
big surprise waiting for him!
WE are the ones who will protect\nthis world—and its future!
